    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is an investment-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD), a masterclass in lightweight engineering and sequential forced induction. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW rotary powerplant, showing stellar compression numbers and a perfectly preserved vacuum control system for the twin Hitachi HT12 turbochargers. The chassis is a testament to 50/50 weight distribution, featuring the factory-spec double-wishbone aluminum suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential with no discernible lash. The five-speed short-throw gearbox offers surgical precision, and the engine bay remains entirely unmolested\u2014a rarity for the platform. Finished in original paint with zero oxidation on the undercarriage, this FD delivers a linear torque curve and the high-RPM harmonics that only a perfectly maintained Wankel engine can provide.",
